parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HDM can cause the low beam headlights to fail, making it difficult or impossible to see the roadway, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The low beam headlights fail to illuminate
the headlights turn on and off intermittently
the headlights go out without warning
the high beam headlights are not affected
the "Lights or Illumination Required" message appears on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Low beam headlights fail to illuminate
high beam headlights work intermittently
headlights dim or flicker
headlights fail to turn on
or headlights turn on randomly when the vehicle is off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, increasing the risk of accidents, and can also prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Key gets stuck in the ignition
key is difficult to turn
vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
airbag warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal becomes stiff
brake pedal feels spongy
ABS and traction control warning lights illuminate
vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to not deploy in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates
passenger airbag light stays on
airbag may not deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various systems in the vehicle to malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Instrument panel fails to illuminate
speedometer fails to work
electrical system malfunctions
vehicle's lights and accessories malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a faulty airbag system, which can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, or the unintended deployment of airbags, causing injuries or accidents.
symptoms: The airbag warning light remains illuminated on the instrument panel
the airbag warning light flashes on and off
the passenger airbag sensor does not work properly
the airbag light comes on and remains on while driving or stopped
the airbag light goes on and off randomly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag sensor can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of an accident, or to deploy unexpectedly, leading to injuries or accidents.
symptoms: The passenger airbag sensor does not work properly
the passenger airbag light does not turn on with a passenger in the seat
the passenger airbag sensor is intermittent
the passenger airbag sensor does not detect the weight of a passenger.
